This paper is likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a technique to improve communication efficiency in Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning (MARL) using variance-based control. It also involves evaluating the proposed method using a set of benchmarks. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as MARL is a subfield of AI and the proposed technique aims to improve the performance of agents in MARL. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as the paper deals with improving communication among agents in MARL. 

It could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the proposed technique involves controlling the variance of exchanged messages between agents. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as MARL is often used in robotics applications and the proposed technique could be useful in improving communication efficiency among robots.
